{{Infobox Politician |name = Ion Buga |image = |caption = |office = Member of the [[Moldovan Parliament]] |term_start = 1990 |term_end = 1994 |predecessor = |successor = |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1935|02|16}} |birth_place = |death_date = |death_place = |party = [[Romanian National Party (Moldova)|Romanian National Party]] |otherparty = [[Popular Front of Moldova]] |spouse = |children = |alma_mater = |profession = |religion = [[Eastern Orthodox Church|Eastern Orthodoxy]] }}
'''Ion Buga''' (born February 16, 1935) is a [[Moldova]]n politician and history professor.
== Biography ==
He served as member of the [[Parliament of Moldova]] in 1990s and president of the [[Romanian National Party (Moldova)|Romanian National Party]] after 2000.
He is a leader of the [[Democratic Forum of Romanians in Moldova]].
