'''Oleh Vitaliyovych Kozerod''' (born 1970) ({{lang-uk|Оле́г Віталійович Козеро́д}}) is a political scientist and history researcher. He came from a Polish-Ukrainian aristocratic family Kazirod bearing the [[Zadora coat of arms]].

Kozerod was born in [[Ukraine]], and has become a political scientist and journalist. For many years he worked as a European reporter for several news agencies, including the World Jewish News Agency. Kozerod graduated from [[Kharkiv University]] in 1993, M.A. (Hist) and Dnipropetrovsk University in 1996, Ph.D. 
Since 2000, he is a D.Litt. candidate and member at the Institute of Political and Ethno-national Studies of the Academy of Sciences of Ukraine.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ipiend.gov.ua/?language=en |title=Home : National Academy Of Sciences Of Ukraine. Kuras Institute Of Political And Ethnic Studies |publisher=Ipiend.gov.ua |date=1991-12-11 |accessdate=2012-11-20}}</ref> Since 2002 - publisher of Achievements Russian newspaper. Since 2001, he is a visiting Fellow and Scholar at the Oxford Center for Hebrew and Jewish Studies,<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.ochjs.ac.uk/ |title=Oxford Centre for Hebrew and Jewish Studies &#124; A Recognised Independent Centre of the University of Oxford |publisher=Ochjs.ac.uk |date= |accessdate=2012-11-20}}</ref> Visiting VWS Fellow The Center for Holocaust and Genocide Studies in Amsterdam (2007) and since 2008, a Academic Visitor at the European Humanities Research Center ([[University of Oxford]]). Since 2003 - Fellow of Kuras Institute of Political and Ethno-national Studies of the Academy of Sciences of Ukraine.

Kozerod is an author of scientific and op-ed articles, and several monographs, including:
* "Perelomnye gody. Evreiskaya obshina Ukrainu v 1919-1929 gg." [Life-Changing Years. Jewish Community in Ukraine 1919-1929], Kharkiv, 1998 - 161 pp
*  "A.I.Denikin's regime and Jewish Population of Ukraine: 1919-1920", Kharkiv, 1997<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jewish-heritage.org/prep53.htm |title=JHS: Preprints and reprints series - preprint 53 (English) |publisher=Jewish-heritage.org |date= |accessdate=2012-11-20 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6IqKJ6de5?url=http://www.jewish-heritage.org/prep53.htm |archivedate=2013-08-13 |df= }}</ref>
* "Evrei Ukrainy v period novoi ekonomicheskoi politiki" [Ukrainian Jews during the New Economic Policy], Kiev, 2002 - 252 pp
* "150 evreiskyh organizazyi Velikobritanii" [150 Jewish Organizations in Great Britain], 2006 -181 pp.
* Genderni Aspekty Istorii Ukrains’kogo Evreistva na prukladi periodu 1920-kh rokiv (Gender Aspects of the History of Ukrainian Jewry, the Case of the 1920s). Kyiv:  Raduga, 2013.- 104 pp.
* Istoriografichni Problemy evreiskoi istorii i filosofii (Historiographical problems of Jewish history and philosophy). Kyiv:  Raduga, 2014.- 190 pp.
* Jewish national community in the context of the integration of Ukrainian society (Kyiv, 2014.- 376 p., coauthored).

Kozerod is an expert in the history of Ukraine, in the field of contemporary policy and national security of Great Britain and the European Union, including the history of the 20th century, terrorism, xenophobia, anti-Semitism and interethnic relations. In 1996, he defended a Ph.D thesis on historiography of the White Movement in Ukraine. In 2009, Kozerod defended a D.Litt. thesis on the history of Ukrainian Jewry.{{cn|date=February 2017}}

He is a member of numerous public and professional international organizations, including the European Association for Jewish Studies,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurojewishstudies.org/ |title=European Association for Jewish Studies - EAJS Online Directory |publisher=Eurojewishstudies.org |date= |accessdate=2012-11-20}}</ref> Royal Historical Society and Oxford University Alumni Society.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.alumni.ox.ac.uk/ |title=Alumni home - University of Oxford |publisher=Alumni.ox.ac.uk |date=2012-11-16 |accessdate=2012-11-20}}</ref>

