{{short description|1993 book by Michael Shute}} {{Infobox book | <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Books --> | name = The Origins of Lonergan's Notion of the Dialectic of History: A Study of Lonergan's Early Writings on History | image = The Origins of Lonergan's Notion of the Dialectic of History.jpg | caption = | authors = [[Michael Shute]] | country = United States | language = English | subject = [[philosophy of history]] | publisher = [[University Press of America]] | pub_date = 1993 | media_type = Print ([[Hardcover]]) | pages = 232 pp. | isbn = 9780819188380 }}
'''''The Origins of Lonergan's Notion of the Dialectic of History: A Study of Lonergan's Early Writings on History''''' is a 1993 book by [[Michael Shute]], in which the author provides "a study of previously unavailable material from the 1930s on the subject of [[history]] by [[Bernard Lonergan]]".<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Liddy |first1=Richard M. |title=The Origins of Lonergan's Notion of the Dialectic of History Michael Shute Baltimore: University Press of America, 1993. 232 p |journal=Studies in Religion/Sciences Religieuses |date=March 1996 |volume=25 |issue=1 |pages=131–132 |doi=10.1177/000842989602500126 |url=https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/abs/10.1177/000842989602500126 |accessdate=12 November 2018 |language=en |issn=0008-4298}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Loptson |first1=Peter |title=The Origins of Lonergan's Notion of the Dialectic of HistoryMichael Shute Lanham, MD: University Press of America, 1993, xxii + 206 pp. |journal=[[Dialogue: Canadian Philosophical Review]] |date=Summer 1996 |volume=35 |issue=3 |pages=633–636 |doi=10.1017/S0012217300008982 |url=https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/dialogue-canadian-philosophical-review-revue-canadienne-de-philosophie/article/origins-of-lonergans-notion-of-the-dialectic-of-historymichael-shute-lanham-md-university-press-of-america-1993-xxii-206-pp/55D71E90ECE71EDE90CB1C2F7C4C3416 |accessdate=12 November 2018 |language=en |issn=1759-0949}}</ref>
