{{Infobox person |birth_name = Zacharie Tshimanga Wa Tshibangu |image = Zacharie Tshimanga Wa Tshibangu 2.jpg |caption = |birth_date = {{birth date|df=yes|1941|10|04}} |birth_place = [[Musefu]], D.R.C |death_date = {{death date and age|df=yes|1985|12|10|1941|10|04}} |death_place = [[Brussels]], Kingdom of Belgium |occupation = Professor,writer,author,scholar |known_for = Historical and Educational Writings on DRC. |spouse = Véronique CHIKWAKA |parents = Camille Tshibangu and Mbelu |children = |religion = |signature = Doctor Tshimanga's Signature.jpg }}
''' Zacharie Tshimanga Wa Tshibangu''' was a [[Democratic Republic of the Congo|Congolese]] historian and writer and co-founder of the SOHIZA in 1974. The first intellectual society created by congoleses.
==Biography== Zacharie Tshimanga Wa Tshibangu was born Octobre 04, 1941, in [[Musefu]]
==Works== Tshimanga Wa Tshibangu published the following works:<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sudoc.abes.fr/DB=2.1//SRCH?IKT=12&TRM=041381580&COOKIE=U10178,Klecteurweb,I250,B341720009+,SY,NLECTEUR+WEBOPC,D2.1,E2aa75a99-0,A,H,R185.156.173.170,FY|title=Catalogue SUDOC|website=www.sudoc.abes.fr|access-date=2017-05-25}}</ref>
